article.headline: San Jose St. 74, Santa Clara 68
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- Adrian Oliver had 23 points and 12 rebounds in helping San Jose State beat Santa Clara 74-68 on Wednesday night. Mac Peterson, a senior making his second career start, matched his career high with 17 points as the Spartans (6-5) won for the third time in four games. Robert Owens added 12 points. Robert Smith had 16 points and Troy Payne scored 15 to lead the Broncos (7-6), who had won three of their previous four. It was the 100th meeting between the teams dating to the 1909-10 season. San Jose State won the first meeting 54-30, but Santa Clara leads the all-time series 71-29. Oliver was 6 of 6 from the foul line and scored a basket in the final 44 seconds to seal the win. Santa Clara led 30-25 at halftime.
